Table 1 reports the computational properties of related work to achieve δ𝛿\delta-accurate solutions.
In terms of the regularized least squared loss, we compare the proposed FedNS and FedNDES with first-order algorithms, and Newton-type FL methods.
FedNS applies to commonly used sketch approaches, e.g. sub-Gaussian, SRHT, and SJLT, while FedNDES only applies to SRHT.
Different sketch types leads to various sketch times on the j𝑗j-th local machine, i.e., 𝒪​(nj​M​k)𝒪subscript𝑛𝑗𝑀𝑘\mathcal{O}(n_{j}Mk) for sub-Gaussian, 𝒪​(nj​M​log⁡k)𝒪subscript𝑛𝑗𝑀𝑘\mathcal{O}(n_{j}M\log k) for SRHT and 𝒪​(nnz​(ϕ​(𝑿j)))𝒪nnzitalic-ϕsubscript𝑿𝑗\mathcal{O}(\text{nnz}(\phi({\boldsymbol{X}}_{j}))) for SJLT.
